,000 people have died from coronavirus in South Africa since the pandemic arrived in the country in March, the health ministry said Saturday. The continent's most industrialised economy, South Africa has registered 553,188 coronavirus infections, more than half of the continental caseload, and the fifth-biggest number of COVID-19… August 9, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"